Enum Particle_cons_idx¶

  • Defined in File constants.h

Enum Documentation¶

enum Particle_cons_idx¶

Values:

enumerator a_geo¶

Geometry coefficients. Coefficient for diameter size calculation

enumerator b_geo¶

Exponent for diameter size calculation

enumerator min_x¶

Minimum size of particle for mean meass calculation.

enumerator min_x_act¶

Minimum size of particle for CCN activation (cloud) and ice activation (ice). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_nuc_homo¶

Minimum size of particle for homogenous nucleation (ice). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_nuc_hetero¶

Minimum size of particle for heterogeneous nucleation (ice). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_melt¶

Minimum size of particle for melting (snow, graupel, ice, hail). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_evap¶

Minimum size of particle for evaporation (rain, snow, graupel, ice). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_freezing¶

Minimum size of particle for freezing (rain, cloud). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_depo¶

Minimum size of particle for vapor deposition (ice, snow, graupel, hail). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_collision¶

Minimum size of particle for ice-ice collision. Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_collection¶

Minimum size of particle for different collision processes (snow, rain, ice, snow, graupel). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_conversion¶

Minimum size of particle for conversion processes (cloud, graupel, ice). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_sedimentation¶

Minimum size of particle for sedimentation (rain, ice, snow, graupel, hail). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator min_x_riming¶

Minimum size of particle for riming (cloud, rain, ice, snow, hail, graupel). Should be the same as min_x but is used to distinguish the influence of those processes.

enumerator max_x¶

Maximum size of particle.

enumerator sc_theta_q¶

Coefficient for ice collision ratio mass.

enumerator sc_delta_q¶

Coefficient for ice collision ratio mass.

enumerator sc_theta_n¶

Coefficient for collision particle number (ice, snow).

enumerator sc_delta_n¶

Coefficient for collision particle number (ice, snow).

enumerator s_vel¶

Variance for the assumed Gaussian velocity distributions used in collection and riming processes.

enumerator a_vel¶

Coefficient for particle velocity.

enumerator b_vel¶

Exponent for particle velocity.

enumerator rho_v¶

Coefficient used in density correction for the increased terminal fall velocity with decreasing air density.

\rho_v = (\rho/\rho_0)^{-\rho_{\text{vel}}}

enumerator c_z¶

Coefficient for 2nd mass moment.

enumerator sc_coll_n¶

Coefficient in graupel self collection and cloud riming.

enumerator cmu0¶

Coefficient for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator cmu1¶

Coefficient for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator cmu2¶

Coefficient for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator cmu3¶

Constant for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator cmu4¶

Constant for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator cmu5¶

Exponent for calculating the shape parameter .

enumerator alpha¶

Constant in rain sedimentation.

enumerator beta¶

Coefficient for rain sedimentation.

enumerator gamma¶

Exponent for rain sedimentation.

enumerator mu¶

Riming parameter.

enumerator d_crit_c¶

Riming parameter.

Inverse of capacity. Coefficient in evaporation and vapor deposition.

Constant for average ventilation. Used in melting and ice-vapor processes.

enumerator b_f¶
